{
  "text": "Gadolinium sesquioxide (gadolinia) was selected for investigation because it has a very high thermal neutron cross section of 40,000 barns [CITATION_1] and high melting temperature of 2350 0 C (6). Gadolinia exists in two crystallographic forms;",
  "citation_candidates": [
